        "title": "Follow up MiniMax M3 pricing and PDF extraction defaults",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nMiniMax M3 support already landed separately. This PR only covers the remaining MiniMax M3 follow-up work.\n\n- add MiniMax M3 tiered pricing metadata and update shared cost calculation so tiered provider pricing is applied at runtime\n- switch MiniMax PDF text extraction defaults to `MiniMax-M3`\n- preserve `/fast` rewriting for `MiniMax-M2.7 -> MiniMax-M2.7-highspeed` while documenting and testing that `MiniMax-M3` has no highspeed variant\n- refresh the remaining MiniMax docs/examples/tests that still pointed at the old M2.7 fallback/default behavior\n\nCloses #88868.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/minimax/model-definitions.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/minimax/onboard.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/llm/providers/stream-wrappers/minimax.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/plugin-sdk/provider-stream.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/models-config.providers.minimax.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/llm/model-utils.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/minimax-docs.test.ts`\n- `pnpm build`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: MiniMax M3 now uses the published tiered pricing during runtime cost calculation, PDF text extraction defaults to M3, and MiniMax fast mode remains an M2.7-only rewrite.\nReal environment tested: local source checkout on branch `codex/minimax-m3-support`.\nExact steps or command run after this patch: the focused Vitest commands above plus `pnpm build`.\nEvidence after fix: MiniMax model-definition tests, provider cost tests, docs tests, and shared cost-calculation tests pass with M3 tiered pricing assertions and the updated PDF extraction default.\nObserved result after fix: M3 billing switches between the `<512K` and `512K-1M` pricing tiers at runtime, MiniMax PDF extraction points at `MiniMax-M3`, and `/fast` keeps `MiniMax-M3` unchanged.\nWhat was not tested: live MiniMax API calls against a real account.\n",
